definition.value: A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-threonine with the amino group of L-asparagine.
A beta-diketone that is licodione in which the hydroxy group at position 2 of the 2,4-dihyroxyphenyl moiety has been converted into the its methyl ether.
A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-threonine with the amino group of L-lysine.
A trihydroxyflavone that is  apigenin substituted by a methoxy group at position 3.
A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-tyrosine with the amino group of L-cysteine.
Any carboxylic acid carrying an unspecified halogen substituent at the 2S-position.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy groups of malonic acid.
